# Environment Configuration Template
# ==================================
# 
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
# 1. Copy this file to: confidential/.env
#    Command: copy .env.example confidential\.env  (Windows)
#    Command: cp .env.example confidential/.env    (Linux/Mac)
# 
# 2. Fill in your actual OAuth credentials and encryption key
# 
# 3. NEVER commit confidential/.env to Git
#    (confidential/ folder is already in .gitignore)
#
# WHY confidential/.env?
# - Keeps actual credentials separate from codebase
# - confidential/ folder is gitignored (safe from accidental commits)
# - Makes credential rotation easier
# - Clear separation between template and actual config
#
# ===== PUBLIC VARIABLES =====
VITE_PUBLIC_BUILDER_KEY=__BUILDER_PUBLIC_KEY__
PING_MESSAGE=pong
PORT=8080

# ===== GMAIL OAUTH2 =====
# Get from: https://console.cloud.google.com
# Steps:
# 1. Create Project > Name it "Emailify"
# 2. APIs & Services > Library > Search "Gmail API" > Enable
# 3. APIs & Services > Credentials > + Create Credentials > OAuth client ID
# 4. Configure OAuth Consent Screen first (External, App name: Emailify, add test users)
# 5. Create Web application > Add Redirect URIs:
#    http://localhost:8080/auth/google/callback
#    https://yourdomain.com/auth/google/callback
# 6. Copy Client ID and Client Secret
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=
GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:8080/auth/google/callback

# ===== MICROSOFT OUTLOOK OAUTH2 =====
# Get from: https://portal.azure.com
# Steps:
# 1. Azure Active Directory > App registrations > + New registration
# 2. Name: Emailify
# 3. Copy Application (client) ID
# 4. Certificates & secrets > + New client secret > Copy VALUE (shown once only!)
# 5. API permissions > + Add permission > Microsoft Graph > mail.read, mail.send, offline_access
# 6. Authentication > Add Redirect URIs:
#    http://localhost:8080/auth/microsoft/callback
#    https://yourdomain.com/auth/microsoft/callback
MICROSOFT_CLIENT_ID=
MICROSOFT_CLIENT_SECRET=
MICROSOFT_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:8080/auth/microsoft/callback

# ===== ENCRYPTION KEY =====
# Generate with one of these commands:
# Node.js: node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
# Python: python3 -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_hex(32))"
# Bash: openssl rand -hex 32
ENCRYPTION_KEY=

# ===== ENVIRONMENT =====
NODE_ENV=development
